column5: Anyone I'd the weird little fish.   Some thing killed it and dropped it near my buddy's farm pond.   About 4 inches long.   Got a weird tail on it
central mud minnow would be my guess, a native species
http://wildlife.ohiodnr.gov/species-and-habitats/species-guide-index/fish/central-mudminnow I am guessing Chris is right.
Thanks chris .  That's it for sure.
It'd be nice to see the true shape of the tail. I was thinking a small snakehead but wouldn't put any money down.
Looks to me like a baby bowfin.
Central Mudminnow for sure. Hopefully the link works. Ontario Freshwater Fishes Database - Central Mudminnow.  Jon
As a kid we found a few of those in rural ditches that you never would have suspected a fish could survive.
Yea this is a small farm pond not verry big.
First time I saw one in my bait bucket I chucked it in the bush for fear of unleashing a baby bowfin on a little brookie lake.
